282void DH_check_standard_parameters(DH *dh) {
283 unsigned i;
284
285 if (dh->p == NULL ||
286 dh->g == NULL ||
287 BN_num_bytes(dh->p) != (1024 / 8) ||
288 BN_cmp(dh->g, &bn_two) != 0) {
289 return;
290 }
291
292 for (i = 0; i < sizeof(dh1024_safe_prime) / sizeof(dh1024_safe_prime[0]);
293 i++) {
294 if (BN_cmp(dh->p, &dh1024_safe_prime[i]) == 0) {
295 /* The well-known DH groups are known to have safe primes. In this case
296 * we can safely reduce the size of the private key. */
297 dh->priv_length = 161;
298 break;
299 }
